WEBVTT

00:00.291 --> 00:03.674
Daniel: I SHOULD HAVE BEEN DOING
THIS FOR THE LAST 20 YEARS.

00:03.674 --> 00:05.676
Miranda: WHAT? EATING
PAIN AU CHOCOLAT FOR BREAKFAST?

00:05.676 --> 00:07.888
NO. LIVING IN PARIS
WITH YOU.

00:07.888 --> 00:09.890
AWW, WE WERE KIDS.
WE WEREN'T READY.

00:09.890 --> 00:13.514
YEAH, WELL,
I'M READY NOW.

00:13.514 --> 00:14.935
WHAT DO YOU SAY
WE GET THE HELL OUT OF HERE

00:14.935 --> 00:16.097
AND WORK OFF
SOME OF THESE PASTRIES?

00:16.097 --> 00:18.399
I HAVE TO REHEARSE.
[ SCOFFS ]

00:18.399 --> 00:20.811
[ LAUGHS ]
HOW MUCH REHEARSAL
COULD YOU POSSIBLY NEED?

00:20.811 --> 00:23.524
YOU COULD TEACH CELLO
TO YO-YO MA.
[ LAUGHS ]

00:23.524 --> 00:25.736
WELL, MAYBE YOU CAN
TAKE SOME OF THAT ENERGY

00:25.736 --> 00:27.448
AND CHANNEL IT
INTO YOUR WRITING.

00:29.110 --> 00:32.453
MM.

00:35.576 --> 00:37.618
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

00:42.753 --> 00:44.835
Drexler: DR. PIERCE.

00:44.835 --> 00:46.467
YES?

00:46.467 --> 00:49.550
YOU'D BE A LOT EASIER TO FIND
IF YOU CARRIED A CELLPHONE.

00:49.550 --> 00:52.383
IF I CARRIED A CELLPHONE,
THE GOVERNMENT COULD TRACK ME.

00:52.383 --> 00:53.594
WHO ARE YOU?

00:53.594 --> 00:55.596
SPECIAL AGENT DREXLER.

00:55.596 --> 00:57.558
I'M THE FBI LEGATE
AT THE U.S. EMBASSY.

00:58.939 --> 01:00.681
YOUR GOVERNMENT
NEEDS YOUR HELP.

01:00.681 --> 01:02.603
HELP WITH WHAT?

01:03.984 --> 01:06.187
WE SHOULD TALK
SOMEPLACE MORE PRIVATE.

01:06.187 --> 01:10.651
I UNDERSTAND YOU'RE LECTURING
TOMORROW AT THE SORBONNE.

01:10.651 --> 01:12.072
IS THE FBI
KEEPING TABS ON ME?

01:12.072 --> 01:14.495
ACTUALLY,
WE ARRANGED THE LECTURE.

01:14.495 --> 01:16.907
WHAT DO YOU MEAN,
YOU ARRANGED IT?

01:16.907 --> 01:19.039
A DELEGATION
OF CHINESE SCIENTISTS

01:19.039 --> 01:20.501
IS VISITING THE SORBONNE.

01:20.501 --> 01:22.703
THEY'RE UNDER
VERY TIGHT SECURITY.

01:22.703 --> 01:25.706
CHINESE GOVERNMENT MINDERS
FOLLOW THEM EVERYWHERE.

01:25.706 --> 01:28.709
A MEMBER OF THE DELEGATION --
A CERTAIN DR. SOONG --

01:28.709 --> 01:31.552
HAS BEEN GRANTED PERMISSION
TO ATTEND YOUR LECTURE.

01:31.552 --> 01:34.175
AFTERWARDS,
DR. SOONG WILL APPROACH YOU,

01:34.175 --> 01:36.807
GIVE YOU A PEN,
AND ASK YOU TO SIGN A BOOK.

01:36.807 --> 01:41.642
WE NEED YOU TO KEEP THE PEN
AND DELIVER IT TO US.

01:41.642 --> 01:44.485
WHY? WHAT'S SO SPECIAL
ABOUT THIS PEN?

01:44.485 --> 01:47.488
THAT IS ON A STRICT
NEED-TO-KNOW BASIS.

01:47.488 --> 01:50.110
[ SCOFFS ] YEAH, WELL,
HERE'S WHAT YOU NEED TO KNOW.

01:50.110 --> 01:53.944
I'M NOT SOME GOVERNMENT LACKEY
WHO BLINDLY FOLLOWS ORDERS.

01:53.944 --> 01:55.406
I'M SORRY, DR. PIERCE.

01:55.406 --> 01:58.239
ALL I CAN SAY IS THAT
THE CONTENTS OF THAT PEN

01:58.239 --> 02:00.871
ARE VITAL
TO NATIONAL SECURITY.

02:13.464 --> 02:15.426
I SHOULD JUST
CANCEL THE DAMN LECTURE.

02:15.426 --> 02:17.558
DANIEL,
IT'S THE SORBONNE.

02:17.558 --> 02:19.180
IT'S ONE OF THE OLDEST,
MOST PRESTIGIOUS

02:19.180 --> 02:20.971
UNIVERSITIES IN EUROPE.

02:20.971 --> 02:23.184
YOU'VE WANTED TO LECTURE THERE
FOR YEARS.

02:23.184 --> 02:25.396
WHY WOULD YOU CANCEL?
BECAUSE I DON'T
WANT TO HELP THE FBI

02:25.396 --> 02:27.107
WITH SOME HALF-ASSED
ESPIONAGE SCHEME.

02:27.107 --> 02:28.359
YOU'D LIKE NOTHING BETTER

02:28.359 --> 02:30.821
THAN TO BE
AN INTERNATIONAL SPY.

02:30.821 --> 02:32.533
YOU'RE JUST MAD
BECAUSE THEY WON'T TELL YOU

02:32.533 --> 02:34.114
WHAT'S SO IMPORTANT
ABOUT THE PEN.

02:34.114 --> 02:35.446
IT MIGHT HAVE A POISON TIP,
YOU KNOW?

02:35.446 --> 02:37.908
OR -- OR --
OR MICROFICHE HIDDEN INSIDE.

02:37.908 --> 02:40.831
I THINK THERE COULD BE SOMETHING
ELSE GOING ON ENTIRELY.

02:40.831 --> 02:42.873
REALLY? WHAT?

02:42.873 --> 02:44.705
DID MIRANDA
SEE THIS AGENT DREXLER?

02:44.705 --> 02:47.087
DID ANYONE?
OH, Y-YOU THINK
I HALLUCINATED HIM?

02:47.087 --> 02:50.090
NO. NO WAY. I'D KNOW.
I-I --
COME ON, DANIEL.

02:50.090 --> 02:52.213
THIS KIND OF SPY PLOT
IS CLASSIC PARANOID FANTASY.

02:52.213 --> 02:53.594
YOU DON'T HAVE MAX AROUND

02:53.594 --> 02:54.845
TO TELL YOU
WHO'S REAL AND WHO'S NOT.

02:54.845 --> 02:57.348
YOU HAVE TO CONSIDER
THE POSSIBILITY

02:57.348 --> 02:58.889
THAT YOU'VE DELUDED
YOURSELF

02:58.889 --> 03:01.642
INTO THINKING THAT YOU'RE FINE
WHEN YOU'RE NOT.

03:04.725 --> 03:06.437
WHO ARE YOU CALLING?
KATE. KATE.

03:06.437 --> 03:08.859
SHE'LL -- SHE'LL CONFIRM
THAT DREXLER IS REAL.

03:08.859 --> 03:11.482
IT'S 6:00 A.M. IN CHICAGO.
SHE'S AN EARLY RISER.

03:11.482 --> 03:12.733
[ Ringing ]

03:12.733 --> 03:14.405
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

03:21.412 --> 03:24.034
IS THAT YOURS OR MINE?
[ SIGHS ]

03:24.034 --> 03:25.826
WHO CARES? WHOEVER IT IS,
THEY'LL CALL BACK.

03:25.826 --> 03:27.037
[ RINGING CONTINUES ]

03:27.037 --> 03:28.168
COME HERE.

03:31.091 --> 03:32.293
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

03:32.293 --> 03:34.715
MR. LEWICKI,
HOW ARE THINGS?

03:34.715 --> 03:36.927
I'M GOOD, DEAN HALEY.
THANK YOU.

03:36.927 --> 03:38.929
WELL, I IMAGINE YOU MUST BE
LIVING THE HIGH LIFE THESE DAYS,

03:38.929 --> 03:41.342
THAT BIG HOUSE
ALL TO YOURSELF.
IT'S PRETTY GREAT, SIR.

03:41.342 --> 03:42.973
YOU KNOW, I'VE GOT
A LOT MORE TIME FOR MY STUDIES,

03:42.973 --> 03:44.605
AND THE BEST PART IS
NOT HAVING TO

03:44.605 --> 03:46.437
WAKE UP AT 5:00 A.M.
TO SLICE GRAPEFRUIT.

03:46.437 --> 03:48.269
THINGS
COULDN'T BE BETTER.

03:48.269 --> 03:50.481
YOU MISS HIM, DON'T YOU?
IS IT THAT OBVIOUS?

03:50.481 --> 03:51.852
WE'VE GOT TO
GET HIM BACK.

03:51.852 --> 03:53.274
LOOK, DOC MADE IT PRETTY CLEAR
WHEN HE QUIT

03:53.274 --> 03:55.115
THAT HE'S NOT INTERESTED
IN A RESEARCH POSITION.

03:55.115 --> 03:57.318
SO UNLESS THE CHANCELLOR'S
GONNA LET HIM TEACH AGAIN,

03:57.318 --> 03:59.740
I DON'T THINK
THAT'S HAPPENING.

04:02.413 --> 04:04.244
Kinney:
"FLAGRANT VIOLATIONS

04:04.244 --> 04:06.246
"OF THE AMERICANS
WITH DISABILITIES ACT

04:06.246 --> 04:07.868
"ARE MORE COMMON
THAN IS WIDELY KNOWN.

04:07.868 --> 04:10.291
MY OWN CASE
IS A PERFECT EXAMPLE."

04:10.291 --> 04:11.752
WHAT THE HELL IS THIS,
PAUL?

04:11.752 --> 04:13.173
IT'S AN OP-ED PIECE
THAT DANIEL PIERCE

04:13.173 --> 04:15.466
IS PLANNING TO PUBLISH
IN THE STAR-HERALD.

04:15.466 --> 04:18.088
HE'S CLAIMING THAT CLMU
DISCRIMINATED AGAINST HIM

04:18.088 --> 04:21.432
AND THAT YOU FORCED HIM OUT
BECAUSE OF HIS MENTAL ILLNESS.

04:21.432 --> 04:23.053
I OFFERED HIM
A RESEARCH-ONLY POSITION.

04:23.053 --> 04:26.977
AND HE TOLD ME, AND I QUOTE,
TO "SHOVE IT UP MY ASS."

04:26.977 --> 04:29.390
I ASKED DANIEL TO HOLD OFF,
BUT HE SAID

04:29.390 --> 04:31.812
HE WANTED THIS PUBLISHED
BEFORE HE FILES THE LAWSUIT.

04:31.812 --> 04:34.194
LAWSUIT? WHAT LAWSUIT?

04:34.194 --> 04:37.898
I ASKED HIM THE SAME QUESTION.
HE WOULDN'T ELABORATE.

04:37.898 --> 04:40.611
ALL RIGHT,
HE CAN HAVE HIS JOB BACK,

04:40.611 --> 04:41.822
BUT I HAVE
ONE CONDITION.

04:41.822 --> 04:43.744
HMM?

04:43.744 --> 04:44.955
APOLOGIZE?
[ SCOFFS ]

04:44.955 --> 04:46.957
DOC IS NEVER
GOING TO APOLOGIZE.

04:46.957 --> 04:49.169
I DID MY JOB, MR. LEWICKI.
NOW YOU DO YOURS.

04:49.169 --> 04:53.173
YOU CAN BE VERY PERSUASIVE
WHEN YOU WANT TO BE.

04:53.173 --> 04:54.965
[ SIGHS ]

04:54.965 --> 04:57.798
[ CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYS ]

05:21.572 --> 05:23.404
I'M IN PARIS.

05:23.404 --> 05:25.245
SO, OF COURSE,
I'M BEING MOCKED BY A MIME.

05:25.245 --> 05:28.619
WHAT A CLICHÃ©.
COULD YOU, UM, GET LOST?

05:28.619 --> 05:31.251
GO, GO. G-- UH...

05:31.251 --> 05:32.873
DISPER-- DISPERSEZ!

05:44.635 --> 05:46.847
Drexler: DR. PIERCE.

05:48.138 --> 05:49.810
[ MUSIC STOPS ]
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

05:49.810 --> 05:51.231
I'VE CONVINCED MY SUPERIORS

05:51.231 --> 05:53.183
TO LET ME TELL YOU MORE
ABOUT THE OPERATION.

05:55.185 --> 05:56.937
I'M LISTENING.

05:56.937 --> 05:59.940
THE CHINESE SCIENTIST THAT
I TOLD YOU ABOUT -- DR. SOONG --

05:59.940 --> 06:01.742
IS A NEUROPHARMACOLOGIST.

06:01.742 --> 06:03.153
HE'S DEVELOPED
A NOOTROPIC DRUG

06:03.153 --> 06:05.406
THAT ENHANCES
LEARNING AND MEMORY.

06:05.406 --> 06:07.868
A SMART PILL?

06:07.868 --> 06:10.080
NO. NO, THERE -- THERE --
THERE'S NEVER BEEN

06:10.080 --> 06:12.292
A NOOTROPIC COMPOUND
THAT COULD WITHSTAND THE RIGORS

06:12.292 --> 06:15.045
OF DOUBLE-BLIND TESTING.
APPARENTLY THIS ONE HAS.

06:15.045 --> 06:17.047
IF THAT'S TRUE,
IT COULD HELP

06:17.047 --> 06:19.299
A LOT OF PEOPLE
WITH NEUROLOGICAL IMPAIRMENTS.

06:19.299 --> 06:21.301
NOT IF THE CHINESE GOVERNMENT
HAS ITS WAY.

06:22.503 --> 06:26.006
THEY WANT TO USE THE DRUG
FOR MILITARY PURPOSES.

06:26.006 --> 06:28.429
OH, LET ME GUESS, TO IMPROVE
THE COGNITIVE FUNCTION

06:28.429 --> 06:30.220
OF THEIR SOLDIERS
ON THE BATTLEFIELD.

06:30.220 --> 06:33.103
BUT DR. SOONG WANTS THE DRUG
TO BE AVAILABLE TO EVERYONE.

06:33.103 --> 06:36.517
IF YOU HELP US,
MY SUPERIORS

06:36.517 --> 06:38.358
WILL DO EVERYTHING
THAT THEY CAN TO MAKE SURE

06:38.358 --> 06:40.320
THAT YOU'RE INVOLVED
IN THE CLINICAL TRIALS.

06:40.320 --> 06:42.733
THIS SOUNDS EXACTLY LIKE
THE KIND OF THING

06:42.733 --> 06:45.576
I'D LIKE TO BE
INVOLVED IN...

06:45.576 --> 06:48.529
WHICH MAKES ME THINK
NATALIE WAS RIGHT ABOUT YOU.

06:48.529 --> 06:50.701
DR. PIERCE, I HOPE YOU HAVEN'T
SPOKEN TO ANYONE ABOUT THIS.

06:50.701 --> 06:53.704
THIS SPY MISSION IS NOTHING MORE
THAN A PARANOID FANTASY,

06:53.704 --> 06:56.707
AND YOU ARE OBVIOUSLY
NOT REAL.
I BEG YOUR PARDON?

06:56.707 --> 06:58.338
HEY, HOW WAS REHEARSAL?
HI.

06:58.338 --> 06:59.960
[ SMOOCHES ] SO GOOD.

06:59.960 --> 07:02.803
WHO WAS, UH,
THAT GUY YOU WERE TALKING TO?

07:05.596 --> 07:07.177
ARE YOU OKAY?

07:07.177 --> 07:08.809
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

07:08.809 --> 07:10.811
HEY! HEY, YOU!

07:10.811 --> 07:12.222
UH...
SERGE.

07:12.222 --> 07:14.815
WHAT DO I DO
WITH THIS PEN ONCE I GET IT?

07:14.815 --> 07:17.017
ON THE NORTH SIDE OF NOTRE DAME,
THERE'S A BRONZE MARKER.

07:17.017 --> 07:19.820
POINT ZERO. THAT'S
THE GEOGRAPHIC CENTER OF PARIS.

07:19.820 --> 07:23.233
WALK 20 PACES DUE WEST,
AND YOU'LL SEE A COBBLESTONE

07:23.233 --> 07:25.065
THAT'S DARKER
THAN THE ONES AROUND IT.

07:25.065 --> 07:27.568
IT'S LOOSE.
HIDE THE PEN UNDER IT.

07:27.568 --> 07:30.531
NOTRE DAME, POINT ZERO,
20 STEPS DUE WEST. I GOT IT.

07:30.531 --> 07:33.283
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATION ]

07:33.283 --> 07:36.286
NO, I WON'T HEAR OF IT. DON'T
WORRY. FRANCOIS IS THE BEST.

07:36.286 --> 07:37.708
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

07:37.708 --> 07:39.339
IT'S REALLY OKAY.
YOU DON'T HAVE TO DO THAT.

07:39.339 --> 07:41.171
OH, PLEASE.
IT WAS ENTIRELY MY FAULT.

07:41.171 --> 07:42.793
BUT I'M SURE FRANCOIS
WILL HAVE YOUR CELLO BACK

07:42.793 --> 07:45.215
IN PLENTY OF TIME
FOR OUR LITTLE TRIP.

07:45.215 --> 07:47.968
I TOLD YOU
I-I CAN'T DO THAT.

07:47.968 --> 07:49.590
DANIEL! OH, THIS IS MY FRIEND
SERGE LOMBART.

07:49.590 --> 07:51.592
HE'S WITH
THE FRENCH MINISTRY OF CULTURE.

07:51.592 --> 07:54.645
AH.
SERGE, DANIEL PIERCE.

07:54.645 --> 07:56.436
MIRANDA'S TOLD ME
SO MUCH ABOUT YOU.

07:56.436 --> 07:59.479
OH. SHE HASN'T
MENTIONED YOU.

07:59.479 --> 08:03.063
YES, WELL, UH...
TRUST ME.

08:03.063 --> 08:05.445
FRANCOIS WILL HAVE
THIS BACK TO YOU IN NO
TIME AT ALL, MY DEAR.

08:05.445 --> 08:09.069
IT WAS A PLEASURE TO MEET YOU,
DR. PIERCE.

08:14.284 --> 08:15.996
HMM.
MM-HMM.

08:15.996 --> 08:19.620
WHAT'S WITH
GÃ©RARD DEPAR-DON'T?
[ CHUCKLES ]

08:19.620 --> 08:21.832
SERGE CAME TO SAY HI
AFTER REHEARSAL.

08:21.832 --> 08:23.834
HE ACCIDENTALLY
KNOCKED OVER MY CELLO.

08:23.834 --> 08:25.465
CRACKED
THE FINGERBOARD.

08:25.465 --> 08:26.887
ACTUALLY,
I WAS WONDERING MORE ABOUT

08:26.887 --> 08:28.508
THAT LITTLE TRIP
HE MENTIONED.

08:28.508 --> 08:30.931
DANIEL PIERCE,
ARE YOU JEALOUS?

08:30.931 --> 08:33.133
NO. MAYBE. A LITTLE.

08:33.133 --> 08:34.975
OH, SERGE
INVITED ME TO PLAY

08:34.975 --> 08:37.397
ON A CULTURAL EXCHANGE TOUR
HE ARRANGED.

08:37.397 --> 08:39.810
WHEN YOU SHOWED UP,
I BOWED OUT.

08:39.810 --> 08:41.231
WHY?

08:41.231 --> 08:42.853
I WAITED A LONG TIME
TO BE WITH YOU.

08:42.853 --> 08:44.274
WHAT DID YOU
EXPECT ME TO DO?

08:44.274 --> 08:46.276
JET OFF TO THE MIDEAST
AND LEAVE YOU ALONE

08:46.276 --> 08:48.278
IN THE MOST ROMANTIC CITY
IN THE WORLD?

08:48.278 --> 08:50.490
MIRANDA,
I ESCAPED THE IVORY TOWER.

08:50.490 --> 08:52.703
THERE'S NOWHERE I HAVE TO BE.
I COULD HAVE GONE WITH YOU.

08:52.703 --> 08:56.326
OH, THE TOUR GOES THROUGH
ISTANBUL, LAHORE, TEHRAN.

08:56.326 --> 08:58.538
IT TOOK MONTHS
TO GET THE VISAS.

08:58.538 --> 08:59.830
OKAY.

08:59.830 --> 09:01.662
SO, WHY DIDN'T YOU
EVEN MENTION IT?

09:01.662 --> 09:03.083
BECAUSE IF YOU'D KNOWN,

09:03.083 --> 09:05.505
YOU WOULD HAVE
INSISTED THAT I GO.

09:05.505 --> 09:08.128
LOOK, I'VE BEEN CHASING
MY CAREER FOR 20 YEARS,

09:08.128 --> 09:09.970
AND I'M THROUGH WITH THAT.

09:09.970 --> 09:13.804
I AM PUTTING US FIRST.

09:15.475 --> 09:21.481
Daniel: "PARIS IS LIKE
LOVE OR ART OR FAITH.

09:21.481 --> 09:25.736
CAN'T BE EXPLAINED, ONLY FELT."

09:25.736 --> 09:27.688
I WAS A KID
WHEN I FIRST HEARD THOSE WORDS

09:27.688 --> 09:29.740
IN A MOVIE -- A GREAT MOVIE.

09:29.740 --> 09:35.155
GENE KELLY WAS MY INTRODUCTION
TO THIS MAGICAL CITY.

09:35.155 --> 09:38.999
MOST PEOPLE ONLY KNOW PARIS
THROUGH ART OR POETRY,

09:38.999 --> 09:43.503
AND THIS CAN CREATE
CERTAIN IDEALIZED EXPECTATIONS

09:43.503 --> 09:45.706
THAT BECOME EMBEDDED
IN OUR NEURAL NETWORKS.

09:45.706 --> 09:48.709
OF COURSE, PARIS ISN'T ALWAYS
WHAT WE SEE IN THE MOVIES.

09:48.709 --> 09:53.263
WAITERS DON'T JUST BURST
INTO SONG AT THE DROP OF A HAT,

09:53.263 --> 09:55.215
NO MATTER HOW MUCH I TIP THEM.
[ LAUGHTER ]

09:55.215 --> 09:57.638
AND, IN EXTREME CASES,

09:57.638 --> 10:00.851
SOME TOURISTS SUFFER
A BIZARRE PATHOLOGICAL REACTION

10:00.851 --> 10:03.483
WHEN THEIR IDEALIZED VERSION
OF THIS CITY

10:03.483 --> 10:06.106
COLLIDES WITH THE REAL THING.

10:06.106 --> 10:08.228
THEY FEEL DISORIENTED,

10:08.228 --> 10:12.232
SUFFER FEELINGS OF DELUSION
AND PARANOIA.

10:17.617 --> 10:21.291
SOME EVEN
EXPERIENCE HALLUCINATIONS.

10:21.291 --> 10:26.376
THIS EXTREME
FORM OF CULTURE SHOCK

10:26.376 --> 10:30.010
IS KNOWN, APPROPRIATELY,
AS PARIS SYNDROME.

10:30.010 --> 10:32.422
WHAT DOES THIS SORT
OF PHENOMENON TEACH US

10:32.422 --> 10:34.845
ABOUT THE BRAIN'S ABILITY --
OR INABILITY --

10:34.845 --> 10:40.060
TO ADAPT TO
THE STRANGE AND THE UNFAMILIAR?

10:43.934 --> 10:48.228
MERCI.

10:48.228 --> 10:50.941
WONDERFUL LECTURE, DANIEL.
THANK YOU, HENRI.

10:50.941 --> 10:53.694
WE MUST HAVE DINNER SOON.

10:53.694 --> 10:55.736
ABSOLUTELY,
PERHAPS SOMEWHERE FRENCH.

11:00.450 --> 11:02.282
BONJOUR.

11:04.204 --> 11:08.498
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

11:21.391 --> 11:23.393
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

11:44.584 --> 11:46.787
[ MUMBLING ]

11:51.461 --> 11:52.963
[ WHISTLES ]

11:52.963 --> 11:54.594
GO AWAY.

11:54.594 --> 11:55.886
[ WHISTLES ]
NON. ALLEZ-VOUS-EN!
NON, NON.

11:55.886 --> 11:57.928
NON. ALLEZ-VOUS-EN.

11:57.928 --> 12:01.011
AU REVOIR.
[ SQUEAKS ]

12:01.011 --> 12:06.226
5, 6, 7,
8, 9, 10...11...

12:40.340 --> 12:41.842
[ TELEPHONE RINGING ]

12:45.936 --> 12:47.767
[ BEEP ]
DR. PIERCE'S RESIDENCE.

12:47.767 --> 12:49.599
DANIEL:
Lewicki, it's me.

12:49.599 --> 12:51.231
DOC!
[ Chuckling ] HEY.

12:51.231 --> 12:52.853
HOW'S PARIS?

12:52.853 --> 12:55.485
IT'S PARIS, LEWICKI.
THAT'S A STUPID QUESTION.

12:55.485 --> 12:57.898
ANY MAIL?
Just bills and junk.

12:57.898 --> 12:59.449
But, Doc,
there is one thing.

12:59.449 --> 13:01.862
SO, DEAN HALEY HAS BEEN
TALKING WITH THE CHANCELLOR,

13:01.862 --> 13:05.665
AND KINNEY HAS AGREED
TO REINSTATE YOU AS A TEACHER.

13:05.665 --> 13:06.957
ALL YOU GOT TO DO
IS CALL HIM, DOC.

13:06.957 --> 13:10.080
WHY WOULD I
CALL THAT ASSHOLE?

13:10.080 --> 13:12.082
I THINK THE CHANCELLOR
JUST WANTS TO TALK TO YOU

13:12.082 --> 13:13.293
ABOUT THE WAY
THINGS WENT DOWN, DOC.

13:13.293 --> 13:15.295
OH, I KNOW. I KNOW.

13:15.295 --> 13:17.717
HE WANTS ME TO APOLOGIZE.
WELL, HE CAN FORGET IT.

13:17.717 --> 13:20.590
I'M NOT GROVELING
IN FRONT OF THAT POMPOUS AIRBAG

13:20.590 --> 13:22.182
FOR A JOB
I DON'T EVEN WANT.

13:22.182 --> 13:25.595
WAIT A MINUTE, DOC. WHAT DO
YOU MEAN, YOU DON'T WANT IT?

13:25.595 --> 13:27.517
Why the hell
would I want to come back?

13:27.517 --> 13:29.729
I MEAN, I'M IN THE
MOST BEAUTIFUL CITY IN THE WORLD

